As the World celebrates World Teachers’ Day under the theme “Teachers: Leading in crisis, reimagining the future”, Basic Education Minister Angie Motshekga took the opportunity to thank the more than 400 000 teachers in South Africa for their work during the pandemic. In the infographic below, SABC News takes a look at the number of teachers in the public sector: TEACHERS IN SOUTH AFRICA 410 000 Teachers in the public education system 25 000 schools across all nine provinces where teachers are placed Teacher training In 2018/2019 the Department of Education approved 13 070 bursaries for students to enroll for initial teacher education in different Universities. UNDER 30 In 2019 a total of 16 461 young and qualified educators were appointed in the Provincial Education Departments. 43,774 teachers trained in computer skills, would start training for new coding curriculums. (function(d){var js, id="pikto-embed-js", ref=d.getElementsByTagName("script")[0];if (d.getElementById(id)) { return;}js=d.createElement("script"); js.id=id; js.async=true;js.src="https://create.piktochart.com/assets/embedding/embed.js";ref.parentNode.insertBefore(js, ref);}(document));